commit af9b1c2569ca8f00164a8854999aab2a7b29f006
Author: bddap-bot <bddap.bot@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 7 05:16:17 2026 -0700

    rl#232: controller button swaps Sally's brain at runtime (demo + GCR)
    
    One swap path (crab_world::policy::cycle_brain) for both surfaces: the
    roster is the primary checkpoint dir ("latest") plus every brain-holding
    subdir (keep-best's best/ today; drop in more run/arch dirs and they join
    the cycle — data-driven, arch from each checkpoint's envelope). A swap
    that refuses to load keeps the current brain; the slot name rides the ONE
    label formatter, so the crab's on-screen brain label (and the GCR
    articulation wire to clients) shows the active slot.
    
    Demo: B / D-pad Left; a policy that hot-follows a live dir follows the
    swapped slot (so "latest" keeps streaming the trainer, "best" tracks
    keep-best promotions). GCR: B / R3 on the solo/host peer — Sally's brain
    selection stays where Sally is simulated; a remote client's button is a
    no-op and its label adopts the host's via articulation.
    
    Both bindings + controls-HUD rows come from the one scheme table per the
    standing controls rule.

